 Focused frontend coverage fixes the exact runtime contract, canonical endpoint, demo isolation, error mapping, retry transitions, and request-generation safeguards. Backend coverage fixes the exact serialized profiles-list contract, nullable values, datetime serialization, and unauthenticated 401 boundary without changing backend business behavior or authorization. DEV-012 adds no writes, redesign, dependency, unrelated client migration, or backend behavior change.
 
+## User Management role assignments read-only slice (DEV-013)
+
+DEV-013 preserves the independent DEV-011 users and DEV-012 profiles sections and adds a third independent section to the registered `/admin` page. With demo mode disabled, it requests `GET /user-management/role-assignments` through the canonical authenticated client, producing `GET /api/v1/user-management/role-assignments`. Successful data must be an array whose objects contain exactly the `UserManagementRoleAssignmentRead` fields: integer `id` and `user_id`; string `role_code`; nullable string `scope_type`; nullable integers `scope_id` and `assigned_by_user_id`; boolean `is_active`; valid ISO datetime string `assigned_at`; and nullable valid ISO datetime string `revoked_at`. Missing, mistyped, additional, or invalid datetime fields are rejected before UI state is updated.
+
+Role-assignment demo records are supplied only through a separate mock loader and never call the backend. Role assignments independently present loading, populated, empty, and retryable error states without coupling their result to users or profiles. Only an active role-assignment request receiving HTTP 401 clears `pk_skdk_token` and navigates to `/login`; stale or unmounted 401 responses cannot clear the session or navigate. A 403 and malformed-response, network, configuration, server, unexpected, stale, and unmounted outcomes preserve the token. Generation invalidation prevents superseded or unmounted role-assignment requests from changing current state or causing side effects.
+
+Focused frontend coverage fixes the exact runtime contract, canonical endpoint, demo isolation, error mapping, retry transitions, active and stale 401 handling, token preservation, and stale/unmounted suppression. Backend coverage fixes the exact serialized role-assignment list contract, nullable values, datetime serialization, and unauthenticated 401 boundary without changing backend business behavior or authorization. DEV-013 adds no writes, redesign, dependency, unrelated client migration, authorization change, or backend behavior change.
+
 Operational prerequisites remain a migrated database with an active user, a valid CORS origin for the deployed frontend, secure HTTPS deployment, a supplied `VITE_API_URL`, and demo mode disabled outside intentional demos. Automated coverage does not replace a manual deployed-browser check with a real backend session.
